commit.message: Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/simsong/dfxml

Dfxml schema 1.3.0 (#62)

* Schema: Track DFXML Schema branch add_partition_system_error

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* objects.py: Whitespace-pad parser enums

This patch causes no functional changes.

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* objects.py: Add parser transition for partition system without containing disk image

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* objects.py: Add parser transition for partition system containing file

The DFXML schema permits a partition system to contain a file, e.g. for
carved files, or possibly for a virtual file representing the partition
table.

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* objects.py: Add error property to PartitionSystemObject, borrowing VolumeObject processing

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* objects.py tests: Add test for PartitionSystemObject error property

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* Schema: Track DFXML Schema branch add_partition_child_of_partition

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* objects.py: Add partition object as child of partition object

This would implement DFXML Schema Issue 33:
https://github.com/dfxml-working-group/dfxml_schema/issues/33

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* objects.py tests: Test adding partition object as child of partition object

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* Schema: Track schema branch add_disk_image_error

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* objects.py: Add error property to disk image object

pop_poststream_elements is similar to the other copies of the function,
except for external-namespace element handling.  The DFXML schema
doesn't have a provision for external-namespace elements at the end of
the child element list at the moment.  If determined to be a bug in the
schema, that can be added in a patch-level release when found necessary.

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* objects.py tests: Test error property on disk image object

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* Schema: Update schema pointer to 'develop'

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* objects.py: Fix empty disk image object serialization

This fixes an error discovered while testing serializing empty objects.

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* Schema: Update schema pointer to 'add_partition_index'

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* objects.py: Add PartitionObject.partition_index property

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* objects.py tests: Test partition object properties

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

* Schema: Update schema pointer to 'develop'

Signed-off-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

Co-authored-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>

commit.message: Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/simsong/dfxml

Tcpflow objects (#61)

* Write first draft of tcpflow extension objects

* Switch implementation away from subclassing FileObject; add unit test

I'm not sure offhand of a clean way to swap in subclasses of FileObject
during an iterative parse.  There may be other discussions to have first
anyway.

* Store scanner results metadata differently

* fixed broken test case

* update

Co-authored-by: Alex Nelson <alexander.nelson@nist.gov>
